Description: One Parts Bill is a new company that will create a nationwide billing network for wholesale automotive parts and accessories venders.
Headquarters Regions: West Coast, Western US
Full Description: One Parts Bill is a new company that will create a nationwide billing network for wholesale automotive parts and accessories venders. In addition to upgrading the venders to a paperless system, their customers will be introduced to a the new concept of a single point billing where they can view invoices from all of the venders they do business with at just one location and even pay their bills with just a click.  This billing system will be paper less, easy to use, safe and secure. Although our system will encompass the entire automotive industry it will still maintain complete security and privacy for both venders as well as customers. It will not be possible for any vendor to see what other venders are selling to any customer. Each vendor and customer will have their own login code. The vendor will be able to view their sales records while customers can review their purchases, credits and payments.  Using todays technology we are able to fully automate the billing process for the parts department of new car dealerships. Our system will automatically log into the dealerships DMS every night and download all newly created invoices into our website where we make those invoices available for their customers to view 24/7, then with just a click their customers will make their payments directly into the dealerships checking account.

Description: xtra xtra is a digital resource distributor for hometown news, photos, and milestone announcements.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: At xtra xtra, users can read, create, and share free announcements and events with all of their favorite communities. xtra xtra was founded by Paul Rooney, an entrepreneur with roots in South Boston who wanted a better way to stay connected with his community. The site launched in April of 2009, and extensive user testing ultimately led to a complete redesign of xtra xtra in the winter of that year.  The result is a sleek and comprehensive website for local announcements and events that features stories from every ZIP code in America as well as over 28,000 schools. With only a few clicks, users can create a free posting and instantly link it to different communities. xtra xtra is like an online version of a local newspaper with stories written by people in the community. The site helps people celebrate, honor, remember, and reconnect with community members and classmates. There is no required registration to view content on the site, and users choosing to create their own milestones can choose from a comprehensive list of milestone categories. All news is big news at xtra xtra, so users are encouraged to post all of the milestones that are important to them.  There are many benefits to sharing announcements online versus creating them elsewhere. There are often delays when one publishes an announcement in a newspaper since printers and publishers work according to their own schedules. xtra xtra posts are instantly available, and one milestone can appear in dozens of communities with one click after users tag their posts to different towns and schools. xtra xtra also adds social media to traditional announcements since milestones can be emailed or shared on Twitter, Facebook, and other sites. Finally, the site is eco-friendly since news can be shared with a wide audience without using any paper. xtra xtra is moving forward with plans to create co-branded partnerships with newspapers. The site has finalized an agreement with Boston.com, the website for The Boston Globe, and relationships with other publications are in the near future. This strategy will benefit the newspaper industry as they rush to deliver hyperlocal content to their online users, and it will also help to expand xtra xtra's brand visibility across the country.
Industry Groups: Content and Publishing, Internet Services, Media and Entertainment, Sales and Marketing

Description: ConstructAteam is a Commercial Real Estate company.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Imagine a targeted website that offers connections to people who work in the commercial development world.  A place to research professionals and create a team who can make a project happen.  A place to control the exchange of documents, information and real estate listings.  One website with multiple functions designed to shorten the cycle of development. They did imagine it!  As co-workers in a small architectural firm in Round Rock, Texas they began brainstorming ways to generate more business and the idea of connecting industry professionals early on in the life of a project was born.  That idea produced the ConstructAteam search engine which will generate a list of targeted professionals for a project by answering a series of questions. Twenty-two targeted roles are accommodated in the membership data base.    Because every project needs property, it seemed logical that Real Estate Listings should be a major component of the site.  Listing properties on ConstructAteam.com gives the Broker or Agent an audience of like-minded individuals.  Ateams can be created to share a listing with selected members privately.  A simple click of the mouse will convert the private or pocket listing to a public listing. The third major component of the website is the ability to securely exchange and store documents. Multiple types of documents, photos and drawings can be shared inside an Ateam of selected invited members.  The files uploaded are protected with 3 layers of security.
